Here's what's in **src/index.js**:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello World');
});

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server running on port 3000');
});

module.exports = app;
```

It's a basic Express.js server that just returns "Hello World" when you访问 the root URL. Nothing related to your research topics here either.

